data.name: IoT for Smart Agriculture
data.description: This group brings together innovators and engineers passionate about applying IoT technologies to revolutionize agriculture. We discuss precision farming, environmental monitoring using sensors, automated irrigation systems, and machine learning models for crop prediction. Members collaborate on Arduino and Raspberry Pi-based projects, develop cloud dashboards for real-time farm data, and explore LoRaWAN for rural connectivity. Topics also include soil moisture sensing, livestock tracking, smart greenhouses, and solar-powered edge computing nodes.
data.tags: Smart Agriculture, Precision Farming, Arduino, Raspberry Pi, Soil Moisture Sensors, LoRaWAN, IoT Cloud Platforms, Edge Computing, Crop Monitoring, Sensor Networks

data.name: Neural Rendering and 3D Scene Reconstruction
data.description: A technical community focused on the intersection of computer vision, deep learning, and graphics rendering. We explore neural radiance fields (NeRFs), differentiable rendering, SLAM systems, and multi-view stereo techniques to generate photo-realistic 3D scenes from sparse inputs. The group actively contributes to open-source libraries, experiments with training models on custom datasets, and discusses advancements in volumetric rendering and depth estimation. We also integrate 3D recon pipelines into AR/VR applications and collaborate on GPU-optimized model deployment.
data.tags: NeRF, Differentiable Rendering, 3D Reconstruction, SLAM, Depth Estimation, AR/VR, Volumetric Rendering, PyTorch3D, Computer Vision, Neural Graphics

data.name: Quantum Computing with Qiskit
data.description: Join quantum enthusiasts, physicists, and developers as we dive into IBM’s Qiskit ecosystem and the world of quantum computing. This group is for anyone looking to understand quantum gates, build quantum circuits, or experiment with Grover’s and Shor’s algorithms on real quantum hardware. We host code jams around variational quantum algorithms, noise modeling, and hybrid quantum-classical workflows. The group encourages open discussion on quantum supremacy, error correction, and the impact of quantum algorithms in chemistry, optimization, and finance.
data.tags: Qiskit, Quantum Circuits, Grover’s Algorithm, Shor’s Algorithm, Quantum Supremacy, Variational Quantum Algorithms, IBM Q, Quantum Error Correction, Quantum Chemistry, Hybrid Computing
